author: Min Zeng
title: Long-Term U.S. Government Bonds Rise, Short End Lower on Fed’s Dudley
text:
Long-term U.S. government bonds strengthened Monday as worries over China’s economic slowdown and its impact on the global economy boosted demand for haven assets.
The price gains were diluted by comments from William Dudley, president of the New York Federal Reserve. Mr. Dudley repeated Fed Chairwoman Janet Yellen’s view last week that an interest-rate increase is likely to happen later this year. Mr. Dudley is a voter on the Fed’s...
